Encode:

The cam itself looked good i would say 6/10, it was already very bright and so i didnt feel the need to touch anything
had a slight flicker which is mostly gone, no additional sharpening as it would have hurt the video
within the first 10mins the cam was occasionally aimed a bit too low, so you could see a top of a chair and the top of a head,cropped a bit off to hide as good as possible, but no biggie
splitted the first mins up in 10 parts and fixed perspective and angle as needed, rest of the movie is just fine and steady and untouched

Audio was another 10/10 line from S4NDM4N, very good
there was no need for cleaning, lipsynced to my video

this will do me till retail/web-dl
